cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.LG, cs.NI

This paper deals with the challenge of scheduling jobs in big data clusters, which is a common problem in distributed computing (cs.DC). The proposed solution, Bounded Priority Fairness (BoPF), involves prioritizing jobs based on their latency and throughput requirements, which involves system optimization (cs.SY) and performance evaluation (cs.PF). The paper also discusses simulations and deployments, which involve data analysis and machine learning (cs.LG) as well as networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
